Sentencas: Micromachined solid-oxide fuel cells (muSOFCs) are among a class of devices being investigated for portable power generation.

Sentencas: Optimization of the performance and reliability of such devices requires robust, scale-dependent, design methodologies.

Sentencas: In this first analysis, we consider the structural design of planar, electrolyte-supported, muSOFCs from the viewpoints of electrochemical performance, mechanical stability and reliability, and thermal behavior.
Titulo: Structural design considerations for micromachined solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of electrolyte thickness on fuel cell performance is evaluated using a simple analytical model.
Titulo: Structural design considerations for micromachined solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Design diagrams that account explicitly for thermal and intrinsic residual stresses are presented to identify geometries that are resistant to fracture and buckling.

Sentencas: Analysis of energy loss due to in-plane heat conduction highlights the importance of efficient thermal isolation in microscale fuel cell design.
